caption.body: Our book show “Early Birds: Selections from the Tony Bill Aviation Library Collection, 1893–1914” has some amazing illustrated covers. Check out this gold embossed cover of “The Romance of Aeronautics: An Interesting Account of the Growth & Achievements of All Kinds of Aerial Craft” by Charles Turner from 1912. “Early Birds: Selections from the Tony Bill Aviation Library Collection” is on display, pre-security, in the Aviation Museum and Library in the International Terminal. The Aviation Museum and Library is open from Sunday through Friday, 10am to 4:30pm.  Charles Cyril Turner “The Romance of Aeronautics: An Interesting Account of the Growth & Achievements of All Kinds of Aerial Craft”  1912 SFO Museum Collection The Tony Bill Aviation Library Collection 2000.160.0740
